==English==
===Etymology===
[[Sanskrit]] ''(satī)'' (lit. ''devoted [[woman]]''), from the fem. ''(sat)'' (''[[true]], [[good]]''). (Eng. usg. 1786 [through [[British English]]])

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌti|-ʌti]]

===Noun===
'''suttee'''
# The [[custom]] and/or act of a [[Hindu]] woman giving herself up to be cremated on her husband's funeral [[pyre]] as a sign of her devotion to her late [[spouse]].

